40. Write a PHP script to remove all characters from a string except a-z A-Z 0-9 or " " using an array.
CODE:
<?php
$text = "Hello@123! Welcome_to PHP 8.0";

// Convert string into an array of characters
$chars = str_split($text);

// Filter the array to allow only letters, numbers, and space
$filtered = array_filter($chars, function($char) {
    return preg_match('/[a-zA-Z0-9 ]/', $char);
});

// Join the filtered array back into a string
$cleaned = implode('', $filtered);

echo $cleaned;
?>

OUTPUT:
Hello123 Welcometo PHP 80
